// solving a nonlinear BVP using finite differences and adaptive grids.  //
// Details of the actual algorithm have been omitted, and some steps     //
// aren't even given as comments.  For example, you'll need to insert    //
// code to keep track of the number of Newton iterations, check whether  //
// the maximum number of Newton iterations has been exceeded, and        //
// populate the coefficient matrix and RHS vector for the linear system. //
// You'll also need to handle several aspects of adapting the grid, such //
// as computing the equidistribution constant, determining where to add  //
// new points, actually adding those points, and interpolating the       //
// previously converged solution to the new grid.  Moreover, some        //
// variables have been set to random numbers.  Some print statements are //
// missing.                                                              //
